summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Liberia and the subregion, 
Welcoming the Secretary-General's report and the inauguration of President Ellen Johnson Sirleaf,
Emphasizing remaining challenges in reintegrating ex-combatants and restructuring Liberia's security sector,
Appreciating ECOWAS and AU's support for the Liberian Peace process,
Welcoming former President Charles Taylor's transfer to the Special Court for Sierra Leone,
Determining the situation in Liberia remains a threat to international peace and security,
Acting under Chapter VII,
1. Extends UNMIL's mandate until 30 September 2006;
2. Extends provisions of paragraph 6 of resolution 1626 for the same period;
3. Reaffirms intention to authorize temporary troop redeployment between UNMIL and UNOCI;
4. Takes note of the Secretary-General's letter and intends to review UNOCI's tasks and troop level by end of April 2006;
5. Requests the Secretary-General to review and present a drawdown plan for UNMIL;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
